===Let Periphas know of the investigation's outcome{{subst:void|<!--500041007-->}}===
{{Mission Description|type=adventure|location="Murmuring Woods" Grove of Epiphany|update|Let Periphas know of the suspicious conclusions from the investigation.}}
{{Dialogue Start}}

;(Talk to Hekate)
;(If {{Mission|Unnatural Death|showChapter=0}} has not been completed)
::'''Panicked Scholar:''' ...The defenses were breached? What happened?! If it were just the black tide, we could have lasted longer...
:::'''Despairing Scholar:''' The black-clad swordmaster followed closely, overwhelming all those who still dared to resist.
:::'''Despairing Scholar:''' He's not just a mindless beast. He was on a mission to obliterate the Grove!
:::This terrain's a natural choke point. Set up some laser cannons from the world beyond the sky on both sides, and we'd have an impenetrable defensive position.
:::Unfortunately, there are no useful defensive facilities here, and the black tide's method of advance is far beyond what ordinary military forces can handle.
:::The only thing that the martyred can do is to use their lives in desperate combat to delay for a very limited time.
:::Before the flood of despair submerges people up to their necks, the roof is their only hope.
:::People pray to their gods here, believing in the 'Leap of Faith' as if it were a lifeline, hoping that it truly exists.
:::The cruel part is... even the most unwavering faith cannot overcome the limits of "this existence" itself.
:::It is said that hide-and-seek is the oldest game for all intelligent life. The hunter needs to hide to approach the prey, and the prey also needs to hide to avoid the enemy.
:::&mdash; But thinking about such things in an area destroyed by the black tide seems too cold-blooded. What kind of unease and despair did the deceased go through... it's hard to imagine.
:::'''Hekate:''' Long time no see. Didn't expect to run into you here.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What a coincidence!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What are you doing here?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Who are you again?
